    <p>SYD­NEY • Argentina’s Pablo Mat­era said he was “deeply ashamed” yes­ter­day af­ter he was stripped of the rugby cap­taincy and sus­pended along with two other play­ers over racist tweets.</p>
    <p>Just weeks af­ter the Pu­mas’ first win over the mighty All Blacks, the Argentina Rugby Union sus­pended Mat­era, Guido Petti and San­ti­ago So­cino.</p>
    <p>In the tweets, since deleted, Mat­era dis­par­aged Bo­li­vian and Paraguayan do­mes­tic work­ers with racial stereo­types.</p>


